The paper discusses the use of a hierarchical coevolutionary genetic algorithm for optimization problems, which is a topic that falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also explores different partnering strategies for recombination and evaluation, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the construction of sub-populations and clusters, which could be considered topics in distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE).
